and cross diagrams. It gets easier with practice, so here are some questions to get you started.
Q1 Describe, in terms of electron transfer, how sodium (Na) and chlorine (Cl)
react to form sodium chloride (NaCl). [3 marks]

and bromine (a Group 7 non-metal) form potassium bromide (KBr). [3 marks]
